Evaluate expression in qenv object.

Source: R/qenv-within.R
within.Rd

Convenience function for evaluating inline code inside the environment of a qenv.

Usage

# S3 method for qenv
within(data, expr, ...)

Arguments

data

qenv object

expr

expression to evaluate

...

name:value pairs to inject values into expr

Value

Returns a qenv object with expr evaluated. If evaluation raises an error, a qenv.error is returned.

Details

This is a wrapper for eval_code that provides a simplified way of passing code for evaluation. It accepts only inline expressions (both simple and compound) and allows for injecting values into expr through the ... argument: as name:value pairs are passed to ..., name in expr will be replaced with value.

Using language objects

Passing language objects to expr is generally not intended but can be achieved with do.call. Only single expressions will work and substitution is not available. See examples.

See also

eval_code, base::within

Examples


q <- new_qenv()

# execute code
q <- within(q, {
  i <- iris
})
q <- within(q, {
  m <- mtcars
  f <- faithful
})
q
#> <environment: 0x555e46dd5670> [L]
#> Parent: <environment: package:checkmate>
#> Bindings:
#> • f: <df[,2]> [L]
#> • i: <df[,5]> [L]
#> • m: <df[,11]> [L]
get_code(q)
#> [1] "i <- iris"                  "m <- mtcars\nf <- faithful"

# inject values into code
q <- new_qenv()
q <- within(q, i <- iris)
within(q, print(dim(subset(i, Species == "virginica"))))
#> [1] 50  5
#> <environment: 0x555e42a051a0> [L]
#> Parent: <environment: package:checkmate>
#> Bindings:
#> • i: <df[,5]> [L]
within(q, print(dim(subset(i, Species == species)))) # fails
#> <qenv.error: object 'species' not found 
#>  when evaluating qenv code:
#> print(dim(subset(i, Species == species)))>
within(q, print(dim(subset(i, Species == species))), species = "versicolor")
#> [1] 50  5
#> <environment: 0x555e424485e0> [L]
#> Parent: <environment: package:checkmate>
#> Bindings:
#> • i: <df[,5]> [L]
species_external <- "versicolor"
within(q, print(dim(subset(i, Species == species))), species = species_external)
#> [1] 50  5
#> <environment: 0x555e41feba60> [L]
#> Parent: <environment: package:checkmate>
#> Bindings:
#> • i: <df[,5]> [L]

# pass language objects
expr <- expression(i <- iris, m <- mtcars)
within(q, expr) # fails
#> <qenv.error: object 'expr' not found 
#>  when evaluating qenv code:
#> expr>
do.call(within, list(q, expr))
#> <environment: 0x555e41085e58> [L]
#> Parent: <environment: package:checkmate>
#> Bindings:
#> • i: <df[,5]> [L]
#> • m: <df[,11]> [L]

exprlist <- list(expression(i <- iris), expression(m <- mtcars))
within(q, exprlist) # fails
#> <qenv.error: object 'exprlist' not found 
#>  when evaluating qenv code:
#> exprlist>
do.call(within, list(q, do.call(c, exprlist)))
#> <environment: 0x555e442b02b8> [L]
#> Parent: <environment: package:checkmate>
#> Bindings:
#> • i: <df[,5]> [L]
#> • m: <df[,11]> [L]
